Alice Gale https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alice_Gale 0 Alice Gale (5 December 1858 – 27 March 1941), was an American actress. She appeared in 11 films between 1916 and 1919. Working with stock theater troupes such as the Grand Stock Company, the Girard Stock Company, and Creston Clarke's company, Gale performed on stage for four decades before making her first film, Sins of Men (1916).She was born in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, and died in Harrisburg, Pennsylvania.
